I've been working on a networking library as of lately, and I wanted to implement RPCs. When I implemented these, I used another library with a name along the lines of Castle.Core to allow me to "hook" into function calls of an object, to allow me to then automatically broadcast RPC calls to the server, or the other way around.

This however, presented a minor issue, where, due to .NET limitations, all objects created had to become a slightly different class(making some debug printing slightly more confusing), and it wasn't particularly fast either.

This is why I am requesting hooks, a simple way to simply run something before a function is called, automatically.

The general idea I have would be something in the likes of:
```cs

Type objectType = someObject.GetType();
// Might not be a real function, but you should get the meaning
MethodInfo[] methods = objectType.GetAllMethodsWithAttribute(typeof(RPCAttribute));

foreach(var method in methods) {

    method.OnCall += (CallContext call, params object[] parameters) => {
        Console.WriteLine("Hooked into RPC of name " + call.method.Name);
        // ...
        call.Continue()
    }

}
```
I didn't give a full description to the API, as that is something I'm not 100% sure of quite yet.
